  "text": "All five files are in the gcc--96dfb333 repo under the gcc/ subdirectory.\n\n1. gcc/passes.def — The master ordered list of all optimization passes. It uses the macros INSERT_PASSES_AFTER, NEXT_PASS, and TERMINATE_PASS_LIST to declare the full pipeline (lowering passes, IPA passes, and per-function passes). Key symbol: NEXT_PASS (the macro that sequences each pass in the pipeline).\n\n2. gcc/passes.cc — The pass manager implementation. It defines the pass_manager class methods (constructor pass_manager::pass_manager, destructor, register_pass, execute_early_local_passes, etc.) and the free function execute_pass_list / execute_pass_list_1 that actually walks the linked list of opt_pass objects and invokes each pass's execute() method. Key symbol: execute_pass_list.\n\n3. gcc/pass_manager.h — The pass manager interface header. It declares the gcc::pass_manager class (inside namespace gcc) with public methods register_pass, register_one_dump_file, get_pass_for_id, dump_passes, dump_profile_report, and the per-pass-list head pointers. Key symbol: pass_manager.\n\n4. gcc/tree-ssa-dce.cc — Implements dead code elimination as a concrete GIMPLE optimization pass. Defines pass_dce_base (a gimple_opt_pass subclass), pass_dce (the standard DCE pass), pass_cd_dce (control-dependence-aware DCE), and the factory function make_pass_dce. Key symbol: pass_dce / make_pass_dce.\n\n5. gcc/tree-pass.h — The tree-SSA pass header. Declares the opt_pass base class (which holds sub/next linked-list pointers and the virtual execute() method), the derived classes gimple_opt_pass, rtl_opt_pass, ipa_opt_pass_d, and simple_ipa_opt_pass, plus extern declarations for all pass factory functions including make_pass_dce and make_pass_cd_dce. Key symbol: opt_pass."
